Make sure PostgreSQL is running locally (update `application.properties` accordingly).

## ☁️ Deploy to AWS (Part 2)

1. Set your AWS credentials in GitHub Secrets:
   - `AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID`
   - `AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY`

2. Push to `main` → GitHub Actions will:
   - Build the JAR
   - Build & push Docker image to ECR
   - Apply Terraform (VPC, EKS, RDS)
   - Deploy to Kubernetes

To deploy manually:

```bash
cd terraform
terraform init && terraform apply -auto-approve

Then configure kubectl and apply:
bash
aws eks update-kubeconfig --region <your-region> --name <cluster-name>
kubectl apply -f k8s/

